==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Proviso
<hw>Pro*vi"so</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Provisos</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L., (it) being provided,
abl. of <ets>provisus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>providere</ets>. See
<er>Provide</er>, and cf. <er>Purview</er>.]</ety> <def>An article or
clause in any statute, agreement, contract, grant, or other writing, by
which a condition is introduced, usually beginning with the word
<xex>provided</xex>; a conditional stipulation that affects an
agreement, contract, law, grant, or the like; <as>as, the contract was
impaired by its <ex>proviso</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He doth deny his prisoners,⟦br⟧
But with <qex>proviso</qex> and exception.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Provisor</ent>⟦br⟧
